  <brief_title>Monoclonal Antibody Treatment for Non-Hodgkin's Lymphoma (Low-Grade)</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Amgen</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Amgen</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Epratuzumab is currently being studied in combination with rituximab, for the treatment of
      patients with low-grade NHL who failed previous chemotherapy and have never received
      rituximab or who received rituximab as a single agent or in combination with chemotherapy as
      their last treatment and who demonstrated a partial response or complete response for at
      least 12 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Completed</overall_status>
